---
import TrustPageShell from '../components/public/TrustPageShell.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Sources and Licenses | CryptoPayMap"
  description="How CryptoPayMap records provenance, evaluates source material, attributes OpenStreetMap, and separates data, text, software, and media licensing."
>
  <TrustPageShell
    eyebrow="Provenance and reuse"
    title="Sources and Licenses"
    description="Source usefulness, verification strength, and reuse rights are separate questions. CryptoPayMap keeps provenance traceable and preserves the license boundary of each public data layer."
  >
    <div class="grid gap-9">
      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5 shadow-sm sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Source principles</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 grid list-disc gap-2 pl-5 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          <li>A source is not automatically proof of current checkout acceptance.</li>
          <li>Source URL, observation date, provenance, and applicable license metadata remain traceable.</li>
          <li>External pages are not republished by default; public records use factual metadata, links, and reviewer-authored summaries.</li>
          <li>Copied directory chains do not become independent evidence merely because the same claim appears in several aggregators.</li>
          <li>Private evidence and submission access never imply public republication rights.</li>
          <li>Unclear rights or provenance prevent public reuse until review resolves the issue.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Common source categories</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          {
            [
              ['Official merchant or service pages', 'Payment pages, help centers, checkout documentation, terms, FAQs, branch pages, and service-plan pages can support a claim when they apply to the listed scope.'],
              ['Payment processors', 'Directories, case studies, documentation, and checkout observations may support a route, but processor capability does not prove merchant-specific activation.'],
              ['OpenStreetMap', 'OSM can provide location identity and candidate-discovery signals. A recent dated observation may be medium evidence; undated tags remain weak evidence.'],
              ['Users and business representatives', 'Payment reports, corrections, source links, evidence, ownership information, and media enter review workflows. Submission does not create an automatic public edit.'],
              ['Directories, maps, news, and articles', 'These sources can identify candidates or historical context, but current acceptance normally needs stronger and more recent support.'],
              ['Archives', 'Public web archives may improve durability where appropriate. Private correspondence, receipts, ownership proof, personal data, and secret status pages are never sent to public archives.'],
            ].map(([title, description]) => (
              <article class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5">
                <h3 class="m-0 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">{title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-muted">{description}</p>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-brand-50 p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Public license layers</h2>
        <div class="mt-5 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full min-w-[42rem] border-collapse text-left text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-border text-ink">
                <th class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Layer</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Treatment</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Examples</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-muted">
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="px-3 py-4 font-semibold text-ink">OSM-derived location data</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">ODbL 1.0 with required attribution and applicable obligations</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">Location identity, address, coordinates, and other identified OSM-derived fields</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="px-3 py-4 font-semibold text-ink">CryptoPayMap acceptance data</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">ODC-By 1.0, to the extent CryptoPayMap owns or can license the applicable database rights</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">Reviewed claims, route classifications, confirmation dates, status, and project-originated registries</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="px-3 py-4 font-semibold text-ink">Project-authored explanatory text</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">CC BY 4.0, where marked and to the extent CryptoPayMap owns or can license the rights</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">How to pay text, methodology explanations, and reviewer-authored summaries</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-4 font-semibold text-ink">Images and media</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">Separate item-level rights basis; not covered automatically by general data or text licenses</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-4">Business photos, submitted gallery images, screenshots, and other approved public derivatives</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">OpenStreetMap attribution</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          OpenStreetMap-derived data remains identifiable and is not relabeled as solely CryptoPayMap data. Where OSM data is used, the standard attribution is shown as <strong class="text-ink">© OpenStreetMap contributors</strong> with a path to the applicable copyright and license information.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          OSM is a source layer, not automatic acceptance confirmation. CryptoPayMap applies its verification requirements separately before an acceptance claim appears as confirmed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-card border border-border bg-surface p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Combined exports keep component boundaries</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-7 text-muted">
          Convenience files such as Places JSON, GeoJSON, and map-pin projections can combine project-originated acceptance data with identified source-derived location fields. A combined file does not erase or replace the license applying to each component. The public manifest and record metadata describe the applicable provenance and license treatment.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 border-t border-border pt-6">
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control bg-brand-600 px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-white no-underline hover:bg-brand-700" href="/data">
          View public data files
        </a>
        <a class="motion-feedback inline-flex min-h-11 items-center rounded-control border border-border px-4 py-2 font-semibold text-ink no-underline hover:bg-brand-50" href="/methodology">
          Verification methodology
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </TrustPageShell>
</BaseLayout>
